All of you are wrong. The trick here is that the human shaped solid plate that you see is made out of "Polyamorphate Insulin". And before someone asks, it is not made out of Insulin but just named after the Scientist who invented the composition. The science here is that this composition is made by a process that involves repeated heating and cooling to create weak spots. When you apply pressure on the weak spot, the entire matter kind of "jellifies" while preserving its shape. And for the same reason, if this guy hands it over to you, you would only be able to penetrate it if you hit the weak spot first that is you may have to insert it in the same order he does. So sometimes, additional measures are in place like a slightly differently tipped stick for the hole that corresponds to the weak spot etc (like a key so that it works only when the magician does it).
